    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-08T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-08T05:00:00-05:00" n="752"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/11–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-08T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 8, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 8—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7406. American Interests—Liberated Italy. Legation’s 5150, August 9, 9 p.m.
                    Foreign Office note November 2 states American representatives, according
                    telegram from Swiss Legation Rome, in <pb facs="1230" n="1216" xml:id="pg_1216"
                    /> southern Italy have taken over completely from October 31, all matters
                    concerning American interests in Rome area. From that date Swiss Legation
                    discontinued payment relief.</p>
                <p>Protection American interests in Florence consular district not yet turned over
                    to American representatives. Accordingly Swiss Consulate that city will continue
                    these functions.<note n="87" xml:id="d752fn87">Telegram 8210, December 18, from
                        Bern, indicated that according to Swiss Foreign Office note of December 16,
                        “Swiss Consulate Florence continues protection of American interests in
                        provinces Florence, Arezzo, Livorno, Pisa, Ravenna, Apuania, Forli, Lucas
                            [<hi rend="italic">Lucca?</hi>], Pistoia, and Siena”
                        (125.7711/12–1844).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
